# Normalize line endings so the repo is stored as LF and checked out as LF on
# every platform. Without this, Windows checkouts get CRLF via core.autocrlf and
# fail `npm run format:check` (the Prettier config sets `endOfLine: "lf"`).
#
# `text=auto` lets Git detect text vs. binary; `eol=lf` forces LF in the working
# tree for detected text files. Lockfiles and binaries are handled explicitly.

* text=auto eol=lf

# Lockfile: text, LF (owned by npm; never CRLF).
package-lock.json text eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize or diff as text.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
